Exercise 3 (Devise a procedure for finding the spring constant of a pen, given the mass of the pen, the "click distance" (how much you push it down to click ), and the height it jumps.).

You have a meter-stick and a phone camera as well. Give a derivation for the spring constant, along with a procedure someone else can follow. Make sure to repeat trials.
